2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes an attention mechanism and filter update strategy for discriminative learning. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with developing a more effective and robust tracking algorithm. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) is a possible category as the paper deals with visual tracking, which is a multimedia application. 
5. cs.RO (Robotics) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper proposes a method that can operate beyond real-time, which could be useful in robotics applications.
